        "id": "8bfcf51da5a11880",
        "text": "[[Version 2]]\nPossible Social Components\nWe can consider adding a  social networking component to the app, later, but *only* after the Siva Siva app V1 is complete and we have a clear picture of the scope required.\nWe don’t want to start engineering this feature within the limited sandbox of a single app.\nIt will take some thought and the vision will only come clear after V1 is done,\nIn any event, we cannot create a framework that requires any more moderation than we already have\nTwitter and Facebook hooks will already be present in the app.\nSerious students who wish to engage in a deeper study may be registered for the Master Course and have access to the Master Course Facebook,\nI would certainly see a Siva Siva face book space all it’s own…or discussion groups or possibly a forum style (async) space. But again, we don’t want to include the engineering for this at this time. If we do, the scope bloat will lead the inability to meet our delivery time frames.\n\n\n\n\nAfter we have *all* the modules for the Siva Siva app done and functional, then we can circle back and look at a robust social networking layer. \nThat said, I am loath to throw wet blankets on good ideas. So if you can constrain the discussion of V1 to a completely self-contained experience that works… and then go “blue sky” on the networking aspect to brainstorm… go ahead… just David needs to understand he is not to write a single line of code on our dime for that layer until we finish this (for three books) and another 2 dozen modules0\n\n\nI.e we don’t want this: \" a Dutch format of education called (I think) “Studiehuis”, where members research a topic together and come up with the answers in a group format with a moderator supervising.”"
